headline.main: U.S. RESTS ITS CASE IN ESPIONAGE TRIAL; End Comes Amid a Chorus of Demands From Defense for Declaration of Mistrial

lead_paragraph: The government rested its case shortly after noon yesterday against fifteen persons, accused of espionage and failure to register as agents of a foreign government, as the Brooklyn spy trial rounded out its sixth week before Judge Mortimer W. Byers and a jury in United States District Court.
abstract: SS Robin Moor's sailing data included in information furnished Sebold by Waalen; mistrial demanded on mention of ss name; Govt rests case
